  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nadd a \"default\" kwargs for dealing with external contracts which don't conform to their interface\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nWe might want to add a \"default\" returnvalue to calls (specific name of keyword subject to bikeshedding). This is a more general mechanism for dealing with contracts which return less data than expected, so we do not have to add a builtin for every ERC20 (or, could be other standards) function implementation which is buggy. something like\r\n```vyper\r\nExternalContract(msg.sender).some_function(<args>, default=False)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe compiler can issue code to fill the return buffer with the `default` value if `returndatasize` is empty.\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @charles-cooper in https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/2753#issuecomment-1092932248_\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n\r\nTBD\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\n\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)",
